Novae Group Examines Possible Merger With Omega Insurance

-- B y   A m b e r e e n   C h o u d h u r y
-- 
2011-05-31T06:49:18Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/novae-group-examines-possible-merger-with-omega-insurance-1-.html
Novae Group Plc (NVA) , a Lloyd’s of London
insurer, is assessing a possible merger with competitor  Omega
Insurance Holdings Ltd. (OIH)   “It is currently undertaking due diligence in evaluating
the merits of proposing a possible merger with Omega,” London-
based Novae said in a statement today. “There is no certainty
that an offer will be forthcoming.”  Novae has a market capitalization of about 240.2 million
pounds ($397.1 million), while Omega Insurance is valued at
about 180.5 million pounds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ambereen Choudhury in London at 
 achoudhury@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Edward Evans at 
 eevans3@bloomberg.net  